 For this question, the correct option was: 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

During the evening, as fall armyworm eats during night,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 while the other options were: 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Early in the morning when it is still cool
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

At noon because sunlight increases chemical performance.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To guard against over-rejection of the null hypothesis due to multiple inference
, outcomes of the knowledge questions were combined into an index, constructed
 as the weighted mean of the individual standardized outcomes, using as
 weights the inverse of the co-variance matrix of the transformed outcomes
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
